cleanContent:
China to test first space docking within two days after launching Shenzhou-8

JIUQUAN, Gansu Province, Sept. 28 (Xinhua) -- China will conduct its first space docking test within two days after launching the Shenzhou-8 unmanned spacecraft, a spokesperson with China's manned space program said Wednesday.China is preparing to launch the Tiangong-1 on Thursday evening as an unmanned space module awaiting space dockings with the Shenzhou-8, -9 and -10 spacecrafts one after another in the next two years.
